      "role": "user",
      "content": "i was just staring at the ceiling thinking about how everything we do—every single thing—is basically just a tiny blip that doesn't even register in the grand scheme of things. like, the universe is so vast and indifferent, and eventually everything just goes dark anyway. it feels kind of stupid to even try, doesn't it? to keep struggling through all this noise when it literally doesn't matter in the end.",
